       Change Summary Explanation
       PU 0604: The FY 2027 request increase of $0.957 will fund software and system interoperability upgrades.

       PU 1427: The FY 2027 request decrease of $15.235M will delay the development and fielding of critical fleet training and assessment capabilities by up to three
       years, directly impacting the Ship Self-Defense System (SSDS) Data Collection and Debrief (DCD) and Enhanced Collection System (ECS) as well as DDG 1000
       platforms. These cuts will also degrade Electronic Warfare training, compromising our ability to counter evolving threats, and risk the loss of skilled personnel due
       to project slowdowns. This ultimately delays the delivery of modernized combat system training and data analysis tools to sailors.

       PU 2124: The FY27 request decrease of $0.223 is due to a reduction in contractor support.

       PU 3093: The FY 2027 request decrease of $41.757M is due to initial fielding of Open-Air Battleshaping (OABS) and decrease in ALLAI and APPA software
       development requirements.




