UAS, GCSs, and training systems.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue to develop, test, and integrate SO-p emerging technology mission kits, mission payloads, weapons and modifications
onto the MQ-9 aircraft for UAS, GSCs, and training systems. The MQ-9 platform is a key airborne enabler and provides a pathway
for A2E capabilities. Enhanced capabilities (i.e., Pods and software) are being developed to continue to evolve the MQ-9 and
meet current operation requirements and while also providing foundational capabilities to meet initial A2E needs.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease of $34.851 million is due to transition of A2E capability funding to PE 1160403BB, Aviation Systems, Project SF100:
