D. Acquisition Strategy
The Communications Modernization Program was split into two phases to accelerate the required capabilities for the 2024 crypto mandates. Development work done to
date was accomplished utilizing a Cost Plus Fixed Fee (CPFF) contract.

The Resilient Positioning, Navigation, and Timing program will provide an M-Code capable GPS receiver, upgraded digital Antenna Electronics, and Resilient GPS/INS
(R-EGI) hardware. Contract strategy will be determined.

The MC-130J STAR XIII CR-2 OFP program will ensure STAR XIII interoperability with AC/HC/MC-130J aircraft and mitigate impacts due to STAR IX Mission Computer
DMS. Contract strategy will be determined.




