The Mission Employment Trainer program will begin development of the Weapons Systems Trainer (WST), Cockpit Procedures
Trainer (CPT), Flight Dynamics Modeling and virtualization of the OFPs and leverage forward compatible software to develop
the MET FoS. Investment in Joint Simulation compatible hardware and Simulatorys Common Architecture and Requirements
(SCARS) On-premises equipment will ensure compatibility of investment. Begin instrumentation of aircraft to obtain flight systems
data to support Level D equivalency.
FY 2027 Plans:
The Mission Employment Trainer program will continue development of the WST, CPT and virtualization of the OFPs and
leverage forward compatible software to develop the MET FoS. Aircraft test points will be conducted as well as investment in flight
dynamic computational models to support Level D equivalency. Real-time analysis of Contractors will occur ensuring performance
and delivery.
