resiliency.
‒ Assessment of inclusion of narrowband technologies into the experimental next-generation resilient network. This may include
(1) leveraging commercial 5G cellular waveforms and (2) technologies enabling space-based UHF broadcast supporting both
legacy and modern user equipment.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increased compared to FY 2026 by $116.351 million due to 1) accelerating Narrowband technologies, specifically 5G for
tactical user equipment compatibility with commercial partners and Low Earth Orbit satellite constellations, 2) conducting initial
requirements and design reviews and procurement of long-lead parts for innovative Ultra High Frequency (UHF) communication
payloads and space vehicle for a Narrowband UHF prototype satellite launch in Medium Earth Orbit (MEO) planned for FY 2030
and 3) delivery of Space Data Network prototype ground trusted network hardware for terrestrial exchange point fielding.
